# Angular Component Conventions

## Creating New Components
- Check if a similar component or pattern already exists in `src/app/shared/` before creating new code.
- Reusable UI elements (avatars, badges, loaders, empty states) belong in `src/app/shared/`.
- Page-level components get their own folder at `src/app/<name>/`.

## Template Rules
- Use `*ngIf` with loading/empty/data states in this order: loading spinner → empty state → content.

```html
<!-- ✅ Correct pattern -->
<div class="loading" *ngIf="loading">...</div>
<div class="empty" *ngIf="!loading && items.length === 0">...</div>
<div class="content" *ngIf="!loading && items.length > 0">...</div>
```

- Never leave pages blank when data is empty — always show an empty state with an icon, title, and helpful text.

## Form Overlays
- Errors from API calls inside overlays must use `formError` (shown inside the overlay), not `errorMessage` (shown on the main page behind the overlay).
- Always clear `formError` when opening a form.
- Show success messages after successful operations via `showSuccess()`.

## Styling
- Component CSS must use global design tokens from `styles.css` via CSS variables.
- Use `position: static !important` on elements that should not inherit the global fixed `header` styling.
- Form overlay z-index must be `99999` to sit above the fixed navbar (`z-index: 9999`).
